I'm bracing for a fight to protect Medicare and Medicaid this year because make no mistake: Republicans will use the debt they created from their #TaxScam to justify deep cuts to Medicare, Medicaid, & other vital services. This was always the long game.

It’s been 101 days since funding for the Children’s Health Insurance Program (#CHIP) expired. That’s 101 days that parents across America have lived in fear that their children will lose their only source of health care coverage.

2018 is going to be an eventful year. Time to get to work to fully fund #CHIP & CHCs, make real infrastructure investments, protect DREAMers, safeguard Medicare & Medicaid, and keep up the fight for #jobsandjustice. There’s no time to waste.

Every vote today for the GOP tax bill was a vote for:
-Raising taxes on 86 million middle-class families
-Taking health coverage away from 13 million people
-Giving 83% of tax cuts to the top 1%
-Increasing the deficit by $1.5 trillion.

I voted NO.
I will be voting NO on the GOP tax bill today because there is a better way to reform our tax code- one that is bipartisan, transparent, and fair for all North Carolinians and Americans.

ICYMI: The House is scheduled for a final vote on the GOP tax bill TOMORROW.  

A few reasons why I will be voting NO:
➡️Raises taxes on millions of working families
➡️Slashes taxes for the wealthiest, explodes deficit
➡️Ransacks Medicare & Medicaid of $1.5 Trillion
Looking forward to seeing Senator-elect Doug Jones take his seat in the Senate.

Food Stamps. Pell Grants. Medicare. Medicaid. The GOP will put them all on the chopping block after their tax bill explodes the deficit. Students, families, and seniors in #NC01 depend on these programs. That is why I remain a "NO" on the GOP tax bill.
